        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 7:30PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 730 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Hoschton, or 7 miles
west of Jefferson, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...40 mph wind and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Jefferson, Commerce, Braselton, Maysville, Hoschton, Pendergrass,
Gillsville, Talmo, Candler, Apple Valley, and Banks Crossing.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. Motorists should
slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
